  "prompt": "Why is M&M's motto \"melts in your mouth, not in your hand\"?",
  "response": "M&M's motto \"melts in your mouth, not in your hand\" was created to highlight the unique selling point of the candy. The slogan emphasizes the hard candy shell that surrounds the chocolate, which prevents the chocolate from melting and creating a mess when held in your hand. This characteristic makes M&M's more convenient and enjoyable to eat compared to other types of chocolate that might melt easily when handled. The motto was introduced in the 1940s and has been an effective marketing tool in distinguishing M&M's from other candies.",
